1
00:00:11,533 --> 00:00:14,733
Ma'am Olive became grumpier,

2
00:00:14,800 --> 00:00:16,767
especially when
her daughter died.

3
00:00:16,833 --> 00:00:18,400
You were there
when I was pregnant

4
00:00:18,467 --> 00:00:20,100
and gave birth to Angela.

5
00:00:20,167 --> 00:00:22,767
They had never heard
of her getting married.

6
00:00:22,833 --> 00:00:24,067
She just suddenly had a child.

7
00:00:24,133 --> 00:00:27,133
I'll pray
that you find your daughter.

8
00:00:27,200 --> 00:00:31,333
And when I find Kayla,
I'll introduce you to her.

9
00:00:31,400 --> 00:00:34,300
Do you mean Olive
just adopted Mookie?

10
00:00:34,400 --> 00:00:36,900
I'm begging you.

11
00:00:36,967 --> 00:00:38,700
Help me bring her back home.

12
00:00:38,767 --> 00:00:40,467
Remember the day
of the landslide?

13
00:00:40,533 --> 00:00:41,433
She's that woman.

14
00:00:41,500 --> 00:00:42,633
She's the one
who took your child.

15
00:00:42,700 --> 00:00:44,800
I'm not done yet!
Why did you stop it?

16
00:00:44,867 --> 00:00:46,767
Reporting to the police
is already risky,

17
00:00:46,833 --> 00:00:47,567
what more doing a livestream.

18
00:00:47,633 --> 00:00:49,733
I have a strong feeling.

19
00:00:49,800 --> 00:00:51,333
Strong feeling about what?

20
00:00:51,400 --> 00:00:56,433
I'm not sure if I should tell
you what I feel right now.

21
00:01:35,300 --> 00:01:36,100
Mom,

22
00:01:37,400 --> 00:01:40,200
I know you're worried about me.

23
00:01:42,133 --> 00:01:44,433
But you don't have to.

24
00:01:45,867 --> 00:01:48,433
Think of yourself first,

25
00:01:48,500 --> 00:01:51,733
especially now that Mom
has gone live on social media.

26
00:01:51,800 --> 00:01:54,367
She announced
you were a kidnapper.

27
00:01:54,433 --> 00:02:00,467
The people might attack you,
or the police might arrest you.

28
00:02:00,533 --> 00:02:02,533
I don't want
that to happen to you.

29
00:02:03,467 --> 00:02:07,000
I don't want
you to get harmed.

30
00:02:07,067 --> 00:02:08,733
Mookie, I'll be careful.

31
00:02:09,767 --> 00:02:11,333
I'll be strong,

32
00:02:11,400 --> 00:02:12,433
especially now that something's

33
00:02:12,500 --> 00:02:14,200
- telling me that...
- Emma.

34
00:02:14,300 --> 00:02:15,100
Emma.

35
00:02:16,867 --> 00:02:18,600
Emma, there's something
you should know.

36
00:02:20,567 --> 00:02:23,567
- Mookie and I are talking.
- No, no, no.

37
00:02:23,633 --> 00:02:25,500
This is about Olive.

38
00:02:25,567 --> 00:02:27,267
Come on.

39
00:02:27,333 --> 00:02:30,167
- Mookie, wait a minute.
- Mookie, wait a minute.

40
00:02:36,300 --> 00:02:37,267
It's Olive...

41
00:02:38,300 --> 00:02:40,033
she's the woman who took Kayla.

42
00:02:41,300 --> 00:02:42,400
It's Olive.

43
00:02:47,400 --> 00:02:48,967
What did you say?

44
00:02:49,067 --> 00:02:51,400
Olive stole our child?

45
00:02:51,467 --> 00:02:52,233
Yes.

46
00:02:52,300 --> 00:02:54,033
Are you sure?

47
00:02:54,100 --> 00:02:56,100
Yes, Emma, Mom.

48
00:02:56,167 --> 00:02:58,733
Bukoy saw
Olive's announcement.

49
00:02:58,800 --> 00:03:00,700
And he remembers her.

50
00:03:00,767 --> 00:03:03,133
Emma, I can never forget
that woman's face.

51
00:03:03,200 --> 00:03:04,767
She took your child.

52
00:03:10,400 --> 00:03:15,400
You made me happy
the first time we met, remember?

53
00:03:15,467 --> 00:03:18,533
And we love the same lullabies.

54
00:03:18,600 --> 00:03:23,767
You know, Mom,
I feel that I'm your daughter.

55
00:03:23,867 --> 00:03:27,300
I really feel
that you're my mother.

56
00:03:31,400 --> 00:03:32,267
Why?

57
00:03:34,867 --> 00:03:37,633
If Olive took our child...

58
00:03:39,367 --> 00:03:41,700
Mookie could be our daughter.

59
00:03:43,500 --> 00:03:45,667
How can you be sure, Emma?

60
00:03:45,733 --> 00:03:49,767
I have a strong feeling
that Mookie is our child.

61
00:03:49,833 --> 00:03:50,933
Emma.

62
00:03:51,000 --> 00:03:54,500
She has a heart-shaped
birthmark on her leg.

63
00:03:54,600 --> 00:03:56,600
I saw it.

64
00:03:56,667 --> 00:03:57,300
What?

65
00:03:58,700 --> 00:04:01,300
Is that why
you were stunned earlier?

66
00:04:04,033 --> 00:04:05,600
Yes, Mom.

67
00:04:05,667 --> 00:04:07,800
Others can also have birthmarks,

68
00:04:07,867 --> 00:04:12,367
but not the heart-shaped
birthmark on Kayla's leg.

69
00:04:13,633 --> 00:04:17,833
That explains why I've been fond
of Mookie since the beginning.

70
00:04:17,900 --> 00:04:20,633
That's why she doesn't
seem a stranger to me.

71
00:04:21,333 --> 00:04:25,233
That's why I get hurt
whenever I see her suffer.

72
00:04:25,300 --> 00:04:26,767
Because she's my child.

73
00:04:26,833 --> 00:04:28,433
Because Mookie is our child.

74
00:04:28,533 --> 00:04:30,900
Dan, she's our daughter.

75
00:04:32,867 --> 00:04:35,200
Mookie is our daughter.

76
00:04:49,500 --> 00:04:51,333
Dumb!

77
00:04:53,033 --> 00:04:54,200
Go on!

78
00:04:54,267 --> 00:04:56,067
Let's watch some other videos.

79
00:04:57,367 --> 00:04:59,133
- Uncle?
- These people.

80
00:04:59,200 --> 00:05:00,000
See.

81
00:05:02,267 --> 00:05:03,867
- Hey.
- Uncle,

82
00:05:04,900 --> 00:05:08,633
can I borrow your phone?

83
00:05:09,533 --> 00:05:11,733
I just need to call someone.

84
00:05:13,000 --> 00:05:14,033
Okay.

85
00:05:14,100 --> 00:05:15,933
You can call without limits.

86
00:05:16,000 --> 00:05:20,333
- Go on. I'll just go to Kutsy.
- Thank you.

87
00:05:20,400 --> 00:05:21,500
- Will you be okay here?
- Yes.

88
00:05:21,567 --> 00:05:23,167
- Okay.
- Thank you.

89
00:05:45,733 --> 00:05:47,467
Mommy?

90
00:05:47,533 --> 00:05:49,267
Mookie, sweetie.

91
00:05:49,333 --> 00:05:52,667
I knew you can't neglect me.

92
00:05:52,733 --> 00:05:53,700
Mommy,

93
00:05:54,633 --> 00:05:57,167
can you please take back what
you said about Mommy Emma

94
00:05:57,233 --> 00:05:58,900
on social media?

95
00:05:58,967 --> 00:06:03,633
She didn't kidnap me.
I went with her on my own.

96
00:06:03,700 --> 00:06:07,200
Is that the only reason
why you called me?

97
00:06:07,300 --> 00:06:10,067
Not because you miss me?

98
00:06:10,133 --> 00:06:13,333
Not because you want
to hear my voice?

99
00:06:13,400 --> 00:06:16,400
Mommy Emma only wants
to help me.

100
00:06:17,667 --> 00:06:20,467
I know she can't hurt me.

101
00:06:20,533 --> 00:06:22,100
She can never do that.

102
00:06:22,167 --> 00:06:25,633
And I don't want her to suffer.

103
00:06:25,700 --> 00:06:27,233
I'm so sorry, sweetie.

104
00:06:30,167 --> 00:06:34,000
I never wanted to do that.

105
00:06:34,067 --> 00:06:35,433
But, sweetie,

106
00:06:36,633 --> 00:06:39,667
I'm so sad because you left me

107
00:06:39,733 --> 00:06:41,367
and you went with that Emma.

108
00:06:41,467 --> 00:06:42,867
That's why I did that.

109
00:06:42,933 --> 00:06:44,667
But...

110
00:06:44,733 --> 00:06:46,633
but I will take everything back.

111
00:06:47,900 --> 00:06:50,267
I will take back
everything I said.

112
00:06:50,333 --> 00:06:53,933
I will tell everyone that your
Mommy Emma isn't a kidnapper.

113
00:06:54,000 --> 00:06:55,267
Would you like that?

114
00:06:55,333 --> 00:06:56,300
Will you do that?

115
00:06:57,400 --> 00:06:59,433
I have one favor to ask,
sweetie.

116
00:07:01,233 --> 00:07:03,433
Can you...

117
00:07:03,500 --> 00:07:04,967
meet me?

118
00:07:08,200 --> 00:07:09,367
Please, sweetie.

119
00:07:10,933 --> 00:07:12,667
I miss you so much.

120
00:07:14,300 --> 00:07:18,200
I just want to see
and hug you again.

121
00:07:18,267 --> 00:07:19,900
Just one last time.

122
00:07:26,333 --> 00:07:27,600
Sorry, Mommy.

123
00:07:30,067 --> 00:07:33,533
I'm not ready yet to see you.

124
00:07:35,200 --> 00:07:36,167
Oh, is that so?

125
00:07:39,067 --> 00:07:41,467
If you don't meet with me...

126
00:07:43,300 --> 00:07:46,367
I'll be the one who'll report
to the police...

127
00:07:47,567 --> 00:07:50,400
about your Mommy Emma's
whereabouts.

128
00:07:51,767 --> 00:07:55,700
I will put her in danger.

129
00:07:55,767 --> 00:07:57,800
I'll make people chase her!

130
00:07:59,600 --> 00:08:01,500
- Until...
- Mommy.

131
00:08:04,067 --> 00:08:05,100
Fine.

132
00:08:07,400 --> 00:08:10,067
Okay, I'll meet you.

133
00:08:13,067 --> 00:08:14,133
Good girl.

134
00:08:15,433 --> 00:08:18,333
Let's meet at Sampaguita Park.

135
00:08:18,400 --> 00:08:21,967
It's near where I saw you,
Emma, and Zayn.

136
00:08:23,000 --> 00:08:26,933
Make sure not to tell anyone.

137
00:08:27,000 --> 00:08:28,100
Or else...

138
00:08:29,600 --> 00:08:32,700
you know what
I'll do to your Mommy Emma.

139
00:08:53,533 --> 00:08:54,667
Mister.

140
00:08:56,233 --> 00:08:57,533
- Yes, Ma'am?
- Mister Gibo.

141
00:08:59,300 --> 00:09:04,133
Mister, can you bring
me to Sampaguita Park?

142
00:09:04,200 --> 00:09:05,400
Sure.

143
00:09:06,800 --> 00:09:07,967
Thank you.

144
00:09:25,967 --> 00:09:29,533
- That's Mookie! Hey, Mookie!
- Mookie! Mookie!

145
00:09:29,633 --> 00:09:32,167
- Gabo, stop!
- Mookie!

146
00:09:32,233 --> 00:09:33,767
- Mookie!
- Mookie!

147
00:09:33,833 --> 00:09:35,933
Where is she going? Mookie!

148
00:09:37,167 --> 00:09:38,200
Mookie!

149
00:09:38,933 --> 00:09:40,067
- Mookie!
- Where's Mookie?

150
00:09:40,133 --> 00:09:41,400
Did you see her?

151
00:09:41,467 --> 00:09:43,433
That's what
we're going to tell you, Emma.

152
00:09:43,500 --> 00:09:47,500
We saw Mookie
in Gabo's tricycle.

153
00:09:47,567 --> 00:09:48,733
Yes.

154
00:09:48,800 --> 00:09:50,500
Why didn't you stop her?

155
00:09:50,567 --> 00:09:51,700
We tried.

156
00:09:51,767 --> 00:09:53,400
But they're gone.

157
00:09:53,467 --> 00:09:54,867
But they can't get anywhere far.

158
00:09:54,933 --> 00:09:56,467
Help me, please. Go with me.

159
00:09:56,533 --> 00:09:58,267
- We must find Mookie.
- Come on, come on.

160
00:09:58,333 --> 00:10:00,233
Let's go. Get in my tricycle.
Hurry.

161
00:10:00,300 --> 00:10:01,267
- Hurry!
- Come on, come on!

162
00:10:01,367 --> 00:10:02,200
Get in.

163
00:10:03,800 --> 00:10:05,667
Hurry up.

164
00:10:05,733 --> 00:10:07,267
We'll message you, okay?

165
00:10:07,333 --> 00:10:09,767
We'll follow you.
We'll follow them, right?

166
00:10:09,833 --> 00:10:13,133
- Hurry up! Faster!
- I'm on it!

167
00:10:20,033 --> 00:10:21,967
Papa Jesus,

168
00:10:22,033 --> 00:10:25,867
please help me convince my mom
not to harm Mommy Emma.

169
00:10:27,167 --> 00:10:31,667
I hope she lets me go
home to Mommy Emma.

170
00:10:31,733 --> 00:10:35,367
It's only with them
that I don't feel alone.

171
00:10:35,467 --> 00:10:37,700
That I have a family.

172
00:10:37,767 --> 00:10:40,200
I hope my mom understands.

173
00:11:17,633 --> 00:11:18,733
Hello, Mang Ando.

174
00:11:20,233 --> 00:11:22,367
Are you sure
the resthouse is ready?

175
00:11:24,467 --> 00:11:25,433
Good.

176
00:11:26,500 --> 00:11:28,000
I'll just get Mookie.

177
00:11:28,900 --> 00:11:30,167
We'll go there straight.

178
00:11:47,467 --> 00:11:48,967
I wonder where Mommy is.

179
00:11:56,967 --> 00:11:58,967
This is where Mookie went.

180
00:11:59,033 --> 00:11:59,600
What?

181
00:12:01,000 --> 00:12:02,600
Here? How?

182
00:12:02,667 --> 00:12:04,967
- Emma, what are you doing?
- Emma!

183
00:12:05,033 --> 00:12:05,833
- Mookie, dear! Mookie!
- She get out first.

184
00:12:05,900 --> 00:12:08,300
- Emma, wait!
- Mookie.

185
00:12:08,367 --> 00:12:11,067
- Mom, I'll follow Emma.
- You should. Go on.

186
00:12:11,133 --> 00:12:13,933
- Excuse me. Let's split.
- Hurry.

187
00:12:14,000 --> 00:12:15,200
- Emma!
- What do we do?

188
00:12:15,300 --> 00:12:17,333
- We should split.
- Yes, that'll be faster.

189
00:12:17,400 --> 00:12:19,200
Go this way. I'll go over there.

190
00:12:19,267 --> 00:12:21,200
- Okay?
- Okay, this way.

191
00:12:21,267 --> 00:12:23,467
- Okay, let's go.
- All right, let's go.

192
00:12:23,533 --> 00:12:24,300
But...

193
00:12:25,633 --> 00:12:26,500
Mookie!

194
00:12:29,667 --> 00:12:30,967
Mister,

195
00:12:31,033 --> 00:12:33,900
did you see a young girl
pass by here?

196
00:12:33,967 --> 00:12:35,700
- Miss!
- Are you sure?

197
00:12:35,767 --> 00:12:37,100
Did you see a kid?

198
00:12:41,333 --> 00:12:42,300
Mookie.

199
00:12:44,633 --> 00:12:46,067
Mommy.

200
00:12:46,133 --> 00:12:47,667
Mookie, sweetie.

201
00:12:47,767 --> 00:12:48,967
Mommy.

202
00:12:49,033 --> 00:12:50,733
Mookie, I miss you so much.

203
00:12:52,700 --> 00:12:55,800
I thought you'd never meet me.

204
00:12:57,000 --> 00:12:59,600
And now that we're together,
Mookie,

205
00:13:00,500 --> 00:13:03,833
I won't let us
be separated again.

206
00:13:05,633 --> 00:13:06,867
Mommy...

207
00:13:06,933 --> 00:13:09,333
now that I'm here,

208
00:13:09,400 --> 00:13:12,767
can you take back what you said
about Mommy Emma?

209
00:13:14,167 --> 00:13:16,000
I'll do that later.

210
00:13:16,067 --> 00:13:16,767
But for now,

211
00:13:17,800 --> 00:13:19,767
let me just enjoy this moment,
sweetie.

212
00:13:20,767 --> 00:13:23,533
I'm so happy to see you again.

213
00:13:23,633 --> 00:13:25,733
I miss you so much, Mookie.

214
00:13:30,133 --> 00:13:31,767
I have a surprise for you.

215
00:13:31,833 --> 00:13:33,667
Come on,
I'll show you something.

216
00:13:33,733 --> 00:13:35,600
- Come with me.
- Mommy.

217
00:13:35,667 --> 00:13:37,267
Can we just stay here?

218
00:13:39,533 --> 00:13:40,633
No.

219
00:13:40,700 --> 00:13:42,400
You'll go with me.

220
00:13:42,467 --> 00:13:44,900
And we'll never
be separated again.

221
00:13:44,967 --> 00:13:45,967
Mookie!

222
00:13:47,900 --> 00:13:49,067
Mookie, dear!

223
00:13:50,967 --> 00:13:52,633
Mookie!

224
00:13:52,700 --> 00:13:54,600
Mookie!

225
00:13:54,700 --> 00:13:56,067
Where's that kid?

226
00:13:57,467 --> 00:13:59,300
Mookie!

227
00:13:59,367 --> 00:14:00,867
Mommy, I don't want to.

228
00:14:00,933 --> 00:14:03,133
I'm not coming with you. Bye.

229
00:14:03,200 --> 00:14:04,433
What do you mean?

230
00:14:04,500 --> 00:14:07,267
I have the right
to you and not Emma!

231
00:14:07,333 --> 00:14:08,400
So you're coming with me!

232
00:14:08,467 --> 00:14:12,300
But you promised if I met you,

233
00:14:12,367 --> 00:14:15,267
you'd take back what you said
about Mommy Emma.

234
00:14:15,333 --> 00:14:18,333
So, Mommy, keep your promise.

235
00:14:18,400 --> 00:14:19,633
Promise?

236
00:14:19,700 --> 00:14:20,833
Why?

237
00:14:20,900 --> 00:14:23,833
Didn't you promise me, too?

238
00:14:23,900 --> 00:14:27,133
You promised
you'd never leave me.

239
00:14:27,200 --> 00:14:29,633
And you still left me, Mookie!

240
00:14:29,733 --> 00:14:30,900
You left me.

241
00:14:30,967 --> 00:14:33,067
- So you must come with me.
- I don't want to, Mommy!

242
00:14:33,133 --> 00:14:36,867
I wouldn't do that
if you hadn't tortured me.

243
00:14:36,933 --> 00:14:40,167
You pushed me to leave you.

244
00:14:40,233 --> 00:14:43,167
Didn't you administer
medicine to me?

245
00:14:43,233 --> 00:14:45,433
So that I wouldn't
be able to walk?

246
00:14:45,500 --> 00:14:48,367
So, I will never go with you.

247
00:14:48,433 --> 00:14:49,500
Bye.

248
00:14:49,567 --> 00:14:52,133
- Mommy, please!
- No! I won't let go of you!

249
00:14:52,200 --> 00:14:53,867
You can never get away from me!

250
00:14:55,733 --> 00:14:58,300
Miss, did you see
a young woman?

251
00:14:58,367 --> 00:15:00,500
Here's her picture. This is her.

252
00:15:01,967 --> 00:15:03,267
She's this tall.
Her skin is tan.

253
00:15:03,333 --> 00:15:06,667
You look like the picture
that Olive showed.

254
00:15:06,733 --> 00:15:08,200
This is you, isn't it?

255
00:15:08,267 --> 00:15:09,900
You're the kidnapper.

256
00:15:09,967 --> 00:15:11,500
It's not me.
I'm not a kidnapper.

257
00:15:11,567 --> 00:15:14,467
- Gina!
- It's not me.

258
00:15:14,533 --> 00:15:15,667
Come here. Isn't that her?

259
00:15:15,733 --> 00:15:18,133
- Mookie!
- Yes, that's her.

260
00:15:18,200 --> 00:15:20,000
- Yes!
- She's the kidnapper.

261
00:15:20,067 --> 00:15:22,800
- She's the kidnapper.
- Come. Hurry.

262
00:15:23,800 --> 00:15:24,733
Emma!

263
00:15:26,433 --> 00:15:27,367
Emma!

264
00:15:30,433 --> 00:15:31,367
Emma!

265
00:15:36,533 --> 00:15:37,400
Emma!

266
00:15:40,033 --> 00:15:41,300
Miss! Miss!

267
00:15:41,367 --> 00:15:42,500
- Come with us!
- Let go of me!

268
00:15:42,567 --> 00:15:44,433
- Come on.
- Why would I go with you?

269
00:15:44,500 --> 00:15:46,167
I'm not a kidnapper. Ouch!

270
00:15:46,233 --> 00:15:47,200
Let go of me!

271
00:15:47,267 --> 00:15:48,633
There's a big bounty
if we catch you!

272
00:15:48,700 --> 00:15:50,700
Miss, you can help us.
Come with us.

273
00:15:50,767 --> 00:15:52,367
We won't hurt you. I promise.

274
00:15:52,433 --> 00:15:55,167
Let go of her. If you don't,
we'll call the police!

275
00:15:55,233 --> 00:15:56,200
We're going to
call the police.

276
00:15:56,267 --> 00:15:57,367
She'll go with us!

277
00:15:58,667 --> 00:16:00,000
Emma!

278
00:16:00,067 --> 00:16:02,267
Let go of me.
I'm not a kidnapper!

279
00:16:02,333 --> 00:16:04,767
I can let you go once
I get the one million.

280
00:16:04,833 --> 00:16:05,867
Jun!

281
00:16:05,933 --> 00:16:06,933
Get the car! Hurry!

282
00:16:07,000 --> 00:16:07,933
- Let's go!
- Let me go, please.

283
00:16:08,000 --> 00:16:10,567
- I dare you to get near! Go on!
- My child.

284
00:16:13,233 --> 00:16:14,533
Emma!

285
00:16:14,600 --> 00:16:15,667
Emma!

286
00:16:15,733 --> 00:16:19,900
Mookie, do everything I want,
and we'll be okay

287
00:16:19,967 --> 00:16:21,167
- just like the old times.
- I don't want to.

288
00:16:21,233 --> 00:16:22,600
- Right? Just obey Mommy,
- I don't want to.

289
00:16:22,667 --> 00:16:24,567
- Please.
- and everything will be okay.

290
00:16:24,633 --> 00:16:26,800
- I don't want to, Mommy!
- Mookie!

291
00:16:26,867 --> 00:16:28,100
Miss Ligaya, help!

292
00:16:28,167 --> 00:16:29,100
- Olive!
- Help!

293
00:16:29,167 --> 00:16:30,867
Where are you
bringing Mookie?

294
00:16:30,933 --> 00:16:32,833
Bring her back to us!

295
00:16:32,900 --> 00:16:34,167
Hey!

296
00:16:34,233 --> 00:16:35,200
Olive!

297
00:16:37,633 --> 00:16:38,933
Let go of my wife!

298
00:16:46,433 --> 00:16:47,000
Dan!

299
00:16:48,233 --> 00:16:50,400
Dan, let's go! Let's run!

300
00:16:59,000 --> 00:16:59,833
Let's go, Dan!

301
00:17:01,367 --> 00:17:02,100
Let's go.

302
00:17:08,633 --> 00:17:12,467
- Over there!
- Mommy!

303
00:17:12,533 --> 00:17:15,200
Mommy, where are we?

304
00:17:15,300 --> 00:17:16,667
Isn't that Olive Caparas?

305
00:17:16,733 --> 00:17:19,333
The one searching
for her daughter?

306
00:17:19,400 --> 00:17:20,333
That's her!

307
00:17:21,900 --> 00:17:23,700
Over here!

308
00:17:45,533 --> 00:17:48,300
- That's Olive Caparas!
- Miss!

309
00:17:48,400 --> 00:17:51,633
Miss, did you see a woman?
Someone with a young girl?

310
00:17:51,700 --> 00:17:52,833
No.

311
00:17:52,900 --> 00:17:53,367
- No?
- No.

312
00:17:53,433 --> 00:17:56,067
Where did they go?

313
00:17:56,133 --> 00:17:56,800
What's that?

314
00:18:03,833 --> 00:18:07,533
Liar! That's them!
You're even recording them!

315
00:18:07,600 --> 00:18:08,600
This is nothing.

316
00:18:08,667 --> 00:18:10,033
- What do you mean nothing!
- It's nothing!

317
00:18:14,967 --> 00:18:15,933
Mom's calling.

318
00:18:16,967 --> 00:18:18,967
- Hello, Mom?
- Hello, Emma?

319
00:18:19,033 --> 00:18:19,800
Where are you?

320
00:18:20,967 --> 00:18:22,700
Did you find them?

321
00:18:22,800 --> 00:18:24,333
I saw Olive.

322
00:18:24,400 --> 00:18:25,867
She's dragging Mookie!

323
00:18:25,933 --> 00:18:27,433
What? Where are you?

324
00:18:27,500 --> 00:18:29,233
Here. What street is this?

325
00:18:29,300 --> 00:18:31,100
San Antonio!

326
00:18:31,167 --> 00:18:34,400
And she brought Mookie
to an abandoned building!

327
00:18:34,467 --> 00:18:36,367
Mom, wait for us.
Don't go anywhere.

328
00:18:36,433 --> 00:18:37,833
Yes. Hurry up!

329
00:18:37,900 --> 00:18:39,500
Go! I'll wait for you!

330
00:18:42,133 --> 00:18:43,133
Hey!

331
00:18:43,200 --> 00:18:44,500
Go, run, Emma!

332
00:18:47,367 --> 00:18:48,733
Find Mookie!

333
00:18:53,033 --> 00:18:53,533
Dan!

334
00:18:54,733 --> 00:18:55,333
Hit him!

335
00:18:58,267 --> 00:18:59,567
Help!

336
00:19:01,500 --> 00:19:03,800
Mommy, please!

337
00:19:03,867 --> 00:19:05,333
Come here. Come on!

338
00:19:05,400 --> 00:19:07,400
- Mommy, please...
- You're giving me a hard time,

339
00:19:07,467 --> 00:19:09,133
we'll stay here for now, okay?

340
00:19:09,200 --> 00:19:11,533
We're going to leave
once they're gone.

341
00:19:11,600 --> 00:19:13,700
Mommy, what are you doing?

342
00:19:13,767 --> 00:19:15,433
There you go, sissies.

343
00:19:15,500 --> 00:19:18,367
Have you watched
Olive Caparas' livestream?

344
00:19:18,433 --> 00:19:20,767
She said Emma Joseco kidnapped

345
00:19:20,833 --> 00:19:22,900
her daughter
Maria Angela Caparas.

346
00:19:22,967 --> 00:19:23,900
And here's the latest!

347
00:19:23,967 --> 00:19:25,833
Brace yourselves!
There's an update!

348
00:19:25,900 --> 00:19:27,067
It'll drive you nuts!

349
00:19:30,033 --> 00:19:33,733
Mommy, I'll never go with you
no matter what you do.

350
00:19:33,800 --> 00:19:36,067
Mookie, you're just saying that

351
00:19:36,133 --> 00:19:40,167
because you've never experienced
hardship with Emma.

352
00:19:40,233 --> 00:19:44,967
I'm the only one who can give
things they can't give you.

353
00:19:45,033 --> 00:19:47,333
I can endure a difficult life.

354
00:19:47,400 --> 00:19:49,567
Despite the life they have,
Mommy Emma and her family

355
00:19:49,633 --> 00:19:54,200
they love me,
and they don't hurt me.

356
00:19:54,267 --> 00:19:55,400
Mom!

357
00:19:55,467 --> 00:19:57,200
- Emma! Hurry up!
- Mom!

358
00:19:57,267 --> 00:19:58,367
Where's Mookie?

359
00:19:58,433 --> 00:20:00,267
Olive and Mookie are there!

360
00:20:00,333 --> 00:20:03,300
- Come on! Let's go there!
- Mom, stay here. Okay?

361
00:20:03,400 --> 00:20:05,000
Wait for Danilo.

362
00:20:05,067 --> 00:20:06,867
- Be careful!
- Yes, Mom!

363
00:20:08,567 --> 00:20:09,400
Mookie!

364
00:20:10,400 --> 00:20:12,300
Mookie, please.

365
00:20:12,367 --> 00:20:14,833
Don't make it hard for us.

366
00:20:14,900 --> 00:20:17,033
Just come with me.

367
00:20:21,833 --> 00:20:23,633
Let go of my daughter!

368
00:20:23,700 --> 00:20:25,567
Mom!

369
00:20:25,633 --> 00:20:26,733
Mom!

370
00:20:26,800 --> 00:20:27,800
Mom!

371
00:20:33,200 --> 00:20:35,533
Are you a leech?

372
00:20:35,633 --> 00:20:38,733
Why don't you leave
my child alone?

373
00:20:38,800 --> 00:20:40,900
Your child has long been dead!

374
00:20:40,967 --> 00:20:42,367
Mookie isn't your child!

375
00:20:42,433 --> 00:20:44,567
You just stole her!

376
00:20:44,633 --> 00:20:45,800
What are you talking about?

377
00:20:45,867 --> 00:20:49,700
You stole Baby Kayla before,
but it will never happen again.

378
00:20:49,767 --> 00:20:52,533
And I will never let you
hurt my daughter again!

379
00:21:03,800 --> 00:21:05,233
Over there!

380
00:21:05,300 --> 00:21:07,000
Please help him!

381
00:21:07,067 --> 00:21:08,767
- Over there!
- Stop it!

382
00:21:10,467 --> 00:21:11,467
Sir, are you okay?

383
00:21:11,533 --> 00:21:13,867
- Danilo.
- Just please catch them, Sir.

384
00:21:13,933 --> 00:21:16,000
I saw you.
That's why I asked for help.

385
00:21:16,067 --> 00:21:17,333
Are you okay?

386
00:21:17,400 --> 00:21:19,367
I need to find Emma.
I need to follow her.

387
00:21:19,433 --> 00:21:20,433
I'll take care
of everything here.

388
00:21:20,500 --> 00:21:22,967
Olive, stop torturing Kayla.

389
00:21:24,500 --> 00:21:25,267
Mom...

390
00:21:26,967 --> 00:21:29,767
Mom, am I Baby Kayla?

391
00:21:29,833 --> 00:21:30,700
Yes, dear.

392
00:21:32,333 --> 00:21:33,633
You are my daughter.

393
00:21:38,033 --> 00:21:40,433
There you have it, sissies.

394
00:21:40,500 --> 00:21:43,600
It's like we're watching
a drama series.

395
00:21:43,700 --> 00:21:45,033
Is that true?

396
00:21:45,100 --> 00:21:47,600
Did Olive Caparas steal
the daughter

397
00:21:47,667 --> 00:21:52,967
of the woman who she has
recently accused of kidnapping?

398
00:21:53,033 --> 00:21:56,167
It's like a drama series.
I cannot.

399
00:21:56,233 --> 00:21:58,167
Ma'am Olive stole
someone else's child?

400
00:21:58,233 --> 00:21:59,300
Is this true?

401
00:22:00,733 --> 00:22:02,200
That's not true.

402
00:22:02,267 --> 00:22:04,000
Ma'am, we didn't notice you.

403
00:22:05,367 --> 00:22:07,500
Olive isn't a kidnapper.

404
00:22:07,567 --> 00:22:12,500
So don't believe those liars,
especially Emma Joseco.

405
00:22:15,967 --> 00:22:17,233
Do you know where...

406
00:22:18,567 --> 00:22:19,667
that place is?

407
00:22:21,067 --> 00:22:22,200
I pass by this place.

408
00:22:22,267 --> 00:22:23,500
It's just near here.

409
00:22:23,567 --> 00:22:25,367
Do you want me
to bring you there?

410
00:22:26,400 --> 00:22:27,267
Let's go.

411
00:22:32,733 --> 00:22:34,833
I thought you were dead.

412
00:22:34,900 --> 00:22:36,633
But no.

413
00:22:36,700 --> 00:22:39,033
That woman stole you from me!

414
00:22:46,233 --> 00:22:48,267
Mommy, is that true?

415
00:22:48,333 --> 00:22:50,433
Is Mommy Emma telling the truth?

416
00:22:50,533 --> 00:22:52,367
- No!
- Is that true?

417
00:22:52,433 --> 00:22:55,100
No, Mookie, believe me.

418
00:22:55,167 --> 00:22:57,500
That woman is lying!

419
00:22:57,567 --> 00:23:00,967
I'm your mother.

420
00:23:01,033 --> 00:23:02,200
Look at me!

421
00:23:02,267 --> 00:23:03,300
I'm your mom!

422
00:23:03,367 --> 00:23:04,333
Liar!

423
00:23:06,933 --> 00:23:09,667
I won't allow you to continue
to torture my child.

424
00:23:09,733 --> 00:23:11,833
I will take her back from you!

425
00:23:11,900 --> 00:23:15,267
I don't know what lies
you're talking about!

426
00:23:15,333 --> 00:23:19,333
Don't try to deny it. Someone
saw you. You stole my child!

427
00:23:19,400 --> 00:23:24,100
Maybe you're getting insane
because of hunger and poverty!

428
00:23:24,200 --> 00:23:26,867
That's why you're crazy and
you're thinking

429
00:23:26,933 --> 00:23:28,367
that my daughter
is your daughter!

430
00:23:29,767 --> 00:23:33,400
You're the one
who's mentally ill.

431
00:23:33,467 --> 00:23:37,133
And I'm glad Kayla
isn't your daughter.

432
00:23:37,200 --> 00:23:39,267
Because she won't get it
from you.

433
00:23:39,333 --> 00:23:40,967
Mookie is my daughter!

434
00:23:45,967 --> 00:23:48,900
You have a birthmark on the back
of your left thigh, Mookie.

435
00:23:52,033 --> 00:23:54,933
Even though I was only with
Baby Kayla for a short time,

436
00:23:55,000 --> 00:23:57,567
I will never forget it.

437
00:23:57,667 --> 00:24:00,000
So there is no doubt
you are my child.

438
00:24:15,900 --> 00:24:19,000
Mookie, I'm your real mother.

439
00:24:26,167 --> 00:24:27,933
Excellent!

440
00:24:28,867 --> 00:24:32,567
You're the best actress,
Miss Emma Joseco.

441
00:24:32,633 --> 00:24:36,867
You've been pretending to be
Mookie's mother for 17 years.

442
00:24:36,933 --> 00:24:37,933
You denied the child

443
00:24:38,000 --> 00:24:40,533
the opportunity
to be with her real parents.

444
00:24:40,600 --> 00:24:44,533
And what's worse, you made
my child's life miserable!

445
00:24:44,600 --> 00:24:46,400
No!

446
00:24:46,467 --> 00:24:49,000
I'm Mookie's mother!

447
00:24:49,067 --> 00:24:51,533
Don't turn the tables on me!

448
00:24:51,600 --> 00:24:53,600
You kidnapped Mookie!

449
00:24:54,667 --> 00:24:56,633
Mommy,

450
00:24:56,700 --> 00:24:58,367
please stop!

451
00:25:00,933 --> 00:25:05,267
So that's the reason
I am so fond of Mommy Emma.

452
00:25:06,500 --> 00:25:12,200
That's why she treats me
like her own daughter.

453
00:25:12,267 --> 00:25:15,900
I believe Mommy Emma.

454
00:25:15,967 --> 00:25:18,533
So, she's my real mother.

455
00:25:19,433 --> 00:25:20,933
Mookie.

456
00:25:21,000 --> 00:25:25,033
Mookie, I'm sorry if it took me
a long time to save you.

457
00:25:25,100 --> 00:25:26,700
I'm sorry, dear.

458
00:25:26,767 --> 00:25:28,567
Mom.

459
00:25:28,633 --> 00:25:31,633
Mom, you don't have
to apologize.

460
00:25:33,600 --> 00:25:34,867
You know...

461
00:25:36,400 --> 00:25:43,833
I ask God every day, Mommy!

462
00:25:43,900 --> 00:25:47,033
Why don't you seem to love me!

463
00:25:47,100 --> 00:25:50,200
It's because
I'm not your real daughter!

464
00:25:50,267 --> 00:25:52,267
I'm not your real daughter!

465
00:25:52,333 --> 00:25:53,867
Why are you like that?

466
00:25:53,933 --> 00:25:56,767
Why are you hurting me?

467
00:25:56,833 --> 00:25:58,900
You kidnapped me!

468
00:25:58,967 --> 00:26:00,800
You're so evil!

469
00:26:00,867 --> 00:26:02,833
You're so evil, Mommy!

470
00:26:02,900 --> 00:26:05,467
So evil!

471
00:26:11,467 --> 00:26:12,633
- Danilo!
- Mom! Mom!

472
00:26:12,700 --> 00:26:14,000
- What were you doing? Hurry!
- Where's Emma?

473
00:26:14,067 --> 00:26:15,367
This way! Come on!

474
00:26:15,433 --> 00:26:16,167
Let's go!

475
00:26:17,567 --> 00:26:18,667
Be careful.

476
00:26:24,967 --> 00:26:28,667
I don't want us to get
separated again, dear.

477
00:26:28,733 --> 00:26:29,867
The kid might fall.

478
00:26:29,933 --> 00:26:31,533
No, Mookie!

479
00:26:31,600 --> 00:26:34,733
Mom. Get me out of here, Mom.
Mom, I don't want...

480
00:26:34,800 --> 00:26:38,367
I don't want
to see her anymore.

481
00:26:38,433 --> 00:26:39,500
Mookie, please.

482
00:26:39,567 --> 00:26:41,000
Come back here, Mookie.

483
00:26:41,067 --> 00:26:43,300
Please. Please.

484
00:26:43,400 --> 00:26:46,033
Dear, we're going
to start a new life.

485
00:26:46,100 --> 00:26:49,067
Whatever hardship you went
through with your mom,

486
00:26:49,133 --> 00:26:52,633
Danilo and I
will slowly erase it.

487
00:26:52,700 --> 00:26:54,500
Don't be afraid.
We're here, okay?

488
00:26:54,567 --> 00:26:55,933
We're here.

489
00:26:58,133 --> 00:26:59,800
No.

490
00:26:59,867 --> 00:27:01,600
Mookie, please.

491
00:27:11,367 --> 00:27:13,367
Let her go!

492
00:27:14,567 --> 00:27:16,533
- Mookie!
- Mookie!

493
00:27:16,633 --> 00:27:17,767
What did this have to happen now

494
00:27:17,833 --> 00:27:18,933
that I've learned
she's my granddaughter?

495
00:27:19,000 --> 00:27:22,067
That she's Baby Kayla.
Then this happened.

496
00:27:22,133 --> 00:27:24,000
Who are the patient's parents?

497
00:27:24,067 --> 00:27:26,000
- Me!
- That's me.

498
00:27:26,067 --> 00:27:27,233
I will now fight you

499
00:27:27,300 --> 00:27:30,567
because I know I have
more rights over her.

500
00:27:30,633 --> 00:27:32,000
In your dreams.

501
00:27:34,500 --> 00:27:37,167
I want Olive to pay
for what she did to us.

502
00:27:37,233 --> 00:27:39,133
My child was stolen from me.

503
00:27:39,200 --> 00:27:40,867
Why am I the bad guy here?

504
00:27:40,933 --> 00:27:42,700
I'm the victim here!

505
00:27:42,767 --> 00:27:44,600
Substantial evidence is needed

506
00:27:44,667 --> 00:27:46,767
to prove that Miss Caparas
is involved.

507
00:27:46,833 --> 00:27:49,433
Only one thing can prove it.

508
00:27:49,533 --> 00:27:51,600
And what's your brilliant idea?

509
00:27:51,667 --> 00:27:52,700
DNA test.

510
00:27:54,633 --> 00:27:57,500
We've looked for you everywhere.

511
00:27:57,567 --> 00:27:59,467
We didn't know
you were just here.

512
00:27:59,533 --> 00:28:01,600
I wish we found it sooner.

513
00:28:03,467 --> 00:28:05,967
- Mookie? What happened, Dan?
- Mookie, dear.

514
00:28:06,033 --> 00:28:08,600
- Dan, our daughter!
- Doc! Nurse!
